Formula One world champion Lewis Hamilton faced a furious backlash last night as he was crowned BBC Sports Personality of the year.

Hamilton became the seventh formula 1 driver to scoop the award beating golfer Rory McIlroy to the post by more than 85,000 votes.

But within minutes of receiving the award amid a standing ovation from guests at the event in Glasgow, the racing driver was being attacked on social media for his status as a tax exile. 

