Furious twitter users took the site to vent their fury that someone who ‘doesn’t even have TV license’ should win such a prestigious BBC award.

Chris Hall wrote: ‘The real travesty is that kids inspired by Lewis Hamilton will never get chances he did thanks to tax-dodgers like him.’

Another critic, John Torrie, added: ‘#SportsPersonality An oxymoron perpetuated by the choice of Lewis Hamilton. Proud to be born British but doesn’t want to live here among us.’

